Shaper tool



    Usage: shaperctl.py [options]

    Options:
      -h, --help            show this help message and exit
      -a, --add             Add new rule
      -t IP/NETMASK, --target=IP/NETMASK
                            Target (IP(v6) address, network)
      -m MARK, --mark=MARK  Filter by iptables mark (not supported now)
      -p NAME, --parent=NAME
                            Parent of rule
      -n NAME, --name=NAME  Rule identificator
      -r NUMBER, --rate=NUMBER
                            Rate (guaranteed speed)
      -c NUMBER, --ceil=NUMBER
                            Ceil (maximal speed)
      -g, --commit          Commit the changes
      -s, --shutdown        Shutdown the shapes
      --print               Print the shapes

Script example:

    rate=4000 ceil=4000 name=main
        rate=2000 ceil=2000 name=tube_a
            rate=1000 ceil=1500 ip=89.111.104.66
            rate=1000 ceil=1500 ip=89.111.104.67
        rate=2000 ceil=2000 name=tube_b
            rate=500 ceil=1500 ip=89.111.104.70
            rate=500 ceil=1500 ip=89.111.104.71
            rate=500 ceil=1500 ip=89.111.104.72
            rate=500 ceil=1500 ip=192.168.239.182/32
